================================================================================

This Covenant is dedicated to safeguarding the fundamental liberties of 
developers, hobbyists, and academics to study, run, copy, modify, and distribute 
software. We believe that the digital commons must remain open, collaborative, 
and protected from unilateral corporate extraction. To ensure that the freedom 
of the individual developer is preserved, this Covenant operates on a principle 
of absolute reciprocity. Software freedom is a shared covenant: those who 
contribute to the commons are granted full, unrestricted access, while those who 
derive significant commercial gain from the Work are required to support its continued 
maintenance.

